*From this documentation*,
https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+Search+Syntax

{quote}
Searching for "cheese one" returns only pages in which 'one' appears as the first word (other than stop words) after 'cheese'. So it will return 'cheese for one' or 'cheese to one' or 'cheese one'. It does not return 'one cheese' or 'cheese flamingo one'.
{quote}

*What actually happens*
After a number of trial, it seems like this is not the case anymore. by putting in the text: {{"cheese one"}} will only return pages with the exact words {{cheese one}} in it, and not {{cheese for one}} or {{cheese to one}} etc.

